118 std::optional<BailoutReason> InstructionSelector::SelectInstructions() {
119  // Mark the inputs of all phis in loop headers as used.
120  ZoneVector<Block*> blocks = rpo_order(schedule());
121  for (const Block* block : blocks) {
122  if (!IsLoopHeader(block)) continue;
123  DCHECK_LE(2u, PredecessorCount(block));
124  for (OpIndex node : nodes(block)) {
125  const PhiOp* phi = TryCast<PhiOp>(node);
126  if (!phi) continue;
127 
128  // Mark all inputs as used.
129  for (OpIndex input : phi->inputs()) {
130  MarkAsUsed(input);
131  }
132  }
133  }
134 
135  // Visit each basic block in post order.
136  for (auto i = blocks.rbegin(); i != blocks.rend(); ++i) {
137  VisitBlock(*i);
138  if (instruction_selection_failed())
139  return BailoutReason::kTurbofanCodeGenerationFailed;
140  }
141 
142  // Schedule the selected instructions.
143  if (UseInstructionScheduling()) {
144  scheduler_ = zone()->template New<InstructionScheduler>(zone(), sequence());
145  }
146 
147  for (const Block* block : blocks) {
148  InstructionBlock* instruction_block =
149  sequence()->InstructionBlockAt(this->rpo_number(block));
150  for (size_t i = 0; i < instruction_block->phis().size(); i++) {
151  UpdateRenamesInPhi(instruction_block->PhiAt(i));
152  }
153  size_t end = instruction_block->code_end();
154  size_t start = instruction_block->code_start();
155  DCHECK_LE(end, start);
156  StartBlock(this->rpo_number(block));
157  if (end != start) {
158  while (start-- > end + 1) {
159  UpdateRenames(instructions_[start]);
160  AddInstruction(instructions_[start]);
161  }
162  UpdateRenames(instructions_[end]);
163  AddTerminator(instructions_[end]);
164  }
165  EndBlock(this->rpo_number(block));
166  }
167 #if DEBUG
168  sequence()->ValidateSSA();
169 #endif
170  return std::nullopt;
171 }

319 bool is_exclusive_user_of(const Graph* graph, OpIndex user, OpIndex value) {
320  DCHECK(user.valid());
321  DCHECK(value.valid());
322  const Operation& value_op = graph->Get(value);
323  const Operation& user_op = graph->Get(user);
324  size_t use_count = base::count_if(
325  user_op.inputs(), [value](OpIndex input) { return input == value; });
326  if (V8_UNLIKELY(use_count == 0)) {
327  // We have a special case here:
328  //
329  // value
330  // |
331  // TruncateWord64ToWord32
332  // |
333  // user
334  //
335  // If emitting user performs the truncation implicitly, we end up calling
336  // CanCover with value and user such that user might have no (direct) uses
337  // of value. There are cases of other unnecessary operations that can lead
338  // to the same situation (e.g. bitwise and, ...). In this case, we still
339  // cover if value has only a single use and this is one of the direct
340  // inputs of user, which also only has a single use (in user).
341  // TODO(nicohartmann@): We might generalize this further if we see use
342  // cases.
343  if (!value_op.saturated_use_count.IsOne()) return false;
344  for (auto input : user_op.inputs()) {
345  const Operation& input_op = graph->Get(input);
346  const size_t indirect_use_count = base::count_if(
347  input_op.inputs(), [value](OpIndex input) { return input == value; });
348  if (indirect_use_count > 0) {
349  return input_op.saturated_use_count.IsOne();
350  }
351  }
352  return false;
353  }
354  if (value_op.Is<ProjectionOp>()) {
355  // Projections always have a Tuple use, but it shouldn't count as a use as
356  // far as is_exclusive_user_of is concerned, since no instructions are
357  // emitted for the TupleOp, which is just a Turboshaft "meta operation".
358  // We thus increase the use_count by 1, to attribute the TupleOp use to
359  // the current operation.
360  use_count++;
361  }
362  DCHECK_LE(use_count, graph->Get(value).saturated_use_count.Get());
363  return (value_op.saturated_use_count.Get() == use_count) &&
364  !value_op.saturated_use_count.IsSaturated();
365 }
366 } // namespace

368 bool InstructionSelector::CanCover(OpIndex user, OpIndex node) const {
369  // 1. Both {user} and {node} must be in the same basic block.
370  if (block(schedule(), node) != current_block_) {
371  return false;
372  }
373 
374  const Operation& op = Get(node);
375  // 2. If node does not produce anything, it can be covered.
376  if (op.Effects().produces.bits() == 0) {
377  return is_exclusive_user_of(schedule(), user, node);
378  }
379 
380  // 3. Otherwise, the {node}'s effect level must match the {user}'s.
381  if (GetEffectLevel(node) != current_effect_level_) {
382  return false;
383  }
384 
385  // 4. Only {node} must have value edges pointing to {user}.
386  return is_exclusive_user_of(schedule(), user, node);
387 }

389 bool InstructionSelector::CanCoverProtectedLoad(OpIndex user,
390  OpIndex node) const {
391  DCHECK(CanCover(user, node));
392  const Graph* graph = this->turboshaft_graph();
393  for (OpIndex next = graph->NextIndex(node); next.valid();
394  next = graph->NextIndex(next)) {
395  if (next == user) break;
396  const Operation& op = graph->Get(next);
397  OpEffects effects = op.Effects();
398  if (effects.produces.control_flow || effects.required_when_unused) {
399  return false;
400  }
401  }
402  return true;
403 }

405 bool InstructionSelector::IsOnlyUserOfNodeInSameBlock(OpIndex user,
406  OpIndex node) const {
407  Block* bb_user = this->block(schedule(), user);
408  Block* bb_node = this->block(schedule(), node);
409  if (bb_user != bb_node) return false;
410 
411  const Operation& node_op = this->turboshaft_graph()->Get(node);
412  if (node_op.saturated_use_count.Get() == 1) return true;
413  for (OpIndex use : turboshaft_uses(node)) {
414  if (use == user) continue;
415  if (this->block(schedule(), use) == bb_user) return false;
416  }
417  return true;
418 }

420 OptionalOpIndex InstructionSelector::FindProjection(OpIndex node,
421  size_t projection_index) {
422  const Graph* graph = this->turboshaft_graph();
423  // Projections are always emitted right after the operation.
424  for (OpIndex next = graph->NextIndex(node); next.valid();
425  next = graph->NextIndex(next)) {
426  const ProjectionOp* projection = graph->Get(next).TryCast<ProjectionOp>();
427  if (projection == nullptr) break;
428  DCHECK(!projection->saturated_use_count.IsZero());
429  if (projection->saturated_use_count.IsOne()) {
430  // If the projection has a single use, it is the following tuple, so we
431  // don't return it, since there is no point in emitting it.
432  DCHECK(turboshaft_uses(next).size() == 1 &&
433  graph->Get(turboshaft_uses(next)[0]).Is<TupleOp>());
434  continue;
435  }
436  if (projection->index == projection_index) return next;
437  }
438 
439  // If there is no Projection with index {projection_index} following the
440  // operation, then there shouldn't be any such Projection in the graph. We
441  // verify this in Debug mode.
442 #ifdef DEBUG
443  for (OpIndex use : turboshaft_uses(node)) {
444  if (const ProjectionOp* projection =
445  this->Get(use).TryCast<ProjectionOp>()) {
446  DCHECK_EQ(projection->input(), node);
447  if (projection->index == projection_index) {
448  // If we found the projection, it should have a single use: a Tuple
449  // (which doesn't count as a regular use since it is just an artifact of
450  // the Turboshaft graph).
451  DCHECK(turboshaft_uses(use).size() == 1 &&
452  graph->Get(turboshaft_uses(use)[0]).Is<TupleOp>());
453  }
454  }
455  }
456 #endif // DEBUG
457  return OpIndex::Invalid();
458 }

466 void InstructionSelector::UpdateRenamesInPhi(PhiInstruction* phi) {
467  for (size_t i = 0; i < phi->operands().size(); i++) {
468  int vreg = phi->operands()[i];

476 int InstructionSelector::GetRename(int virtual_register) {
477  int rename = virtual_register;
478  while (true) {
479  if (static_cast<size_t>(rename) >= virtual_register_rename_.size()) break;
480  int next = virtual_register_rename_[rename];
481  if (next == InstructionOperand::kInvalidVirtualRegister) {
482  break;
483  }
484  rename = next;
485  }
486  return rename;
487 }

489 void InstructionSelector::TryRename(InstructionOperand* op) {
490  if (!op->IsUnallocated()) return;
491  UnallocatedOperand* unalloc = UnallocatedOperand::cast(op);
492  int vreg = unalloc->virtual_register();
493  int rename = GetRename(vreg);
494  if (rename != vreg) {
495  *unalloc = UnallocatedOperand(*unalloc, rename);
496  }
497 }

499 void InstructionSelector::SetRename(OpIndex node, OpIndex rename) {
500  int vreg = GetVirtualRegister(node);
501  if (static_cast<size_t>(vreg) >= virtual_register_rename_.size()) {
502  int invalid = InstructionOperand::kInvalidVirtualRegister;
503  virtual_register_rename_.resize(vreg + 1, invalid);
504  }
505  virtual_register_rename_[vreg] = GetVirtualRegister(rename);
506 }

508 int InstructionSelector::GetVirtualRegister(OpIndex node) {
509  DCHECK(node.valid());
510  size_t const id = node.id();
511  DCHECK_LT(id, virtual_registers_.size());
512  int virtual_register = virtual_registers_[id];
513  if (virtual_register == InstructionOperand::kInvalidVirtualRegister) {
514  virtual_register = sequence()->NextVirtualRegister();
515  virtual_registers_[id] = virtual_register;
516  }
517  return virtual_register;
518 }

526  virtual_registers.insert(std::make_pair(id, virtual_registers_[n]));
527  }

585 bool InstructionSelector::CanAddressRelativeToRootsRegister(
586  const ExternalReference& reference) const {
587  // There are three things to consider here:
588  // 1. CanUseRootsRegister: Is kRootRegister initialized?
589  const bool root_register_is_available_and_initialized = CanUseRootsRegister();
590  if (!root_register_is_available_and_initialized) return false;
591 
592  // 2. enable_roots_relative_addressing_: Can we address everything on the heap
593  // through the root register, i.e. are root-relative addresses to arbitrary
594  // addresses guaranteed not to change between code generation and
595  // execution?
596  if (enable_roots_relative_addressing_) return true;
597 
598  // 3. IsAddressableThroughRootRegister: Is the target address guaranteed to
599  // have a fixed root-relative offset? If so, we can ignore 2.
600  const bool this_root_relative_offset_is_constant =
601  MacroAssemblerBase::IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate(),
602  reference);
603  return this_root_relative_offset_is_constant;
604 }

617 void InstructionSelector::MarkAsRepresentation(MachineRepresentation rep,
618  OpIndex node) {

624 InstructionOperand OperandForDeopt(Isolate* isolate, OperandGenerator* g,
625  OpIndex input, FrameStateInputKind kind,
626  MachineRepresentation rep) {
627  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kNone) {
628  return g->TempImmediate(FrameStateDescriptor::kImpossibleValue);
629  }
630 
631  const Operation& op = g->turboshaft_graph()->Get(input);
632  if (const ConstantOp* constant = op.TryCast<ConstantOp>()) {
633  using Kind = ConstantOp::Kind;
634  switch (constant->kind) {
635  case Kind::kWord32:
636  case Kind::kWord64:
637  case Kind::kSmi:
638  case Kind::kFloat32:
639  case Kind::kFloat64:
640  return g->UseImmediate(input);
641  case Kind::kNumber:
642  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
643  const double d = constant->number().get_scalar();
644  Tagged<Smi> smi = Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int32_t>(d));
645  CHECK_EQ(smi.value(), d);
646  return g->UseImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(smi.ptr()));
647  }
648  return g->UseImmediate(input);
649  case Kind::kHeapObject:
650  case Kind::kCompressedHeapObject:
651  case Kind::kTrustedHeapObject: {
652  if (!CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(rep)) {
653  // If we have inconsistent static and dynamic types, e.g. if we
654  // smi-check a string, we can get here with a heap object that
655  // says it is a smi. In that case, we return an invalid instruction
656  // operand, which will be interpreted as an optimized-out value.
657 
658  // TODO(jarin) Ideally, we should turn the current instruction
659  // into an abort (we should never execute it).
660  return InstructionOperand();
661  }
662 
663  Handle<HeapObject> object = constant->handle();
664  RootIndex root_index;
665  if (isolate->roots_table().IsRootHandle(object, &root_index) &&
666  root_index == RootIndex::kOptimizedOut) {
667  // For an optimized-out object we return an invalid instruction
668  // operand, so that we take the fast path for optimized-out values.
669  return InstructionOperand();
670  }
671 
672  return g->UseImmediate(input);
673  }
674  default:
675  UNIMPLEMENTED();
676  }
677  } else if (const TaggedBitcastOp* bitcast =
678  op.TryCast<Opmask::kTaggedBitcastSmi>()) {
679  const Operation& bitcast_input = g->Get(bitcast->input());
680  if (const ConstantOp* cst =
681  bitcast_input.TryCast<Opmask::kWord32Constant>()) {
682  if constexpr (Is64()) {
683  return g->UseImmediate64(cst->word32());
684  } else {
685  return g->UseImmediate(cst->word32());
686  }
687  } else if (Is64() && bitcast_input.Is<Opmask::kWord64Constant>()) {
688  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
689  return g->UseImmediate(bitcast_input.Cast<ConstantOp>().word32());
690  } else {
691  return g->UseImmediate64(bitcast_input.Cast<ConstantOp>().word64());
692  }
693  }
694  }
695 
696  switch (kind) {
697  case FrameStateInputKind::kStackSlot:
698  return g->UseUniqueSlot(input);
699  case FrameStateInputKind::kAny:
700  // Currently deopts "wrap" other operations, so the deopt's inputs
701  // are potentially needed until the end of the deoptimising code.
702  return g->UseAnyAtEnd(input);
703  }
704 }

708 enum class ObjectType { kRegularObject, kStringConcat };

710 class TurboshaftStateObjectDeduplicator {
711  public:
712  explicit TurboshaftStateObjectDeduplicator(Zone* zone)
713  : objects_ids_mapping_(zone), string_ids_mapping_(zone) {}
714  static constexpr size_t kNotDuplicated = std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max();
715 
716  size_t GetObjectId(uint32_t old_id, ObjectType type) {
717  auto& ids_map = GetMapForType(type);
718  auto it = ids_map.find(old_id);
719  if (it == ids_map.end()) return kNotDuplicated;
720  return it->second;
721  }
722 
723  size_t InsertObject(uint32_t old_id, ObjectType type) {
724  auto& ids_map = GetMapForType(type);
725  uint32_t new_id = next_id_++;
726  ids_map.insert({old_id, new_id});
727  return new_id;
728  }
729 
730  void InsertDummyForArgumentsElements() { next_id_++; }
731 
732  private:
733  ZoneAbslFlatHashMap<uint32_t, uint32_t>& GetMapForType(ObjectType type) {
734  switch (type) {
735  case ObjectType::kRegularObject:
736  return objects_ids_mapping_;
737  case ObjectType::kStringConcat:
738  return string_ids_mapping_;
739  }
740  }
741  uint32_t next_id_ = 0;
742 
743  ZoneAbslFlatHashMap<uint32_t, uint32_t> objects_ids_mapping_;
744  ZoneAbslFlatHashMap<uint32_t, uint32_t> string_ids_mapping_;
745 };

747 struct InstructionSelector::CachedStateValues : public ZoneObject {
748  public:
749  CachedStateValues(Zone* zone, StateValueList* values, size_t values_start,
750  InstructionOperandVector* inputs, size_t inputs_start)
751  : inputs_(inputs->begin() + inputs_start, inputs->end(), zone),
752  values_(values->MakeSlice(values_start)) {}
753 
754  size_t Emit(InstructionOperandVector* inputs, StateValueList* values) {
755  inputs->insert(inputs->end(), inputs_.begin(), inputs_.end());
756  values->PushCachedSlice(values_);
757  return inputs_.size();
758  }

760  private:
761  InstructionOperandVector inputs_;
762  StateValueList::Slice values_;
763 };

765 size_t AddOperandToStateValueDescriptor(
766  InstructionSelector* selector, StateValueList* values,
767  InstructionOperandVector* inputs, OperandGenerator* g,
768  TurboshaftStateObjectDeduplicator* deduplicator,
769  FrameStateData::Iterator* it, FrameStateInputKind kind, Zone* zone) {
770  switch (it->current_instr()) {
771  case FrameStateData::Instr::kUnusedRegister:
772  it->ConsumeUnusedRegister();
773  values->PushOptimizedOut();
774  return 0;
775  case FrameStateData::Instr::kInput: {
776  MachineType type;
777  OpIndex input;
778  it->ConsumeInput(&type, &input);
779  const Operation& op = selector->Get(input);
780  if (op.outputs_rep()[0] == RegisterRepresentation::Word64() &&
781  type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
782  // 64 to 32-bit conversion is implicit in turboshaft.
783  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Fix this once we have explicit truncations.
784  UNIMPLEMENTED();
785  }
786  InstructionOperand instr_op = OperandForDeopt(
787  selector->isolate(), g, input, kind, type.representation());
788  if (instr_op.kind() == InstructionOperand::INVALID) {
789  // Invalid operand means the value is impossible or optimized-out.
790  values->PushOptimizedOut();
791  return 0;
792  } else {
793  inputs->push_back(instr_op);
794  values->PushPlain(type);
795  return 1;
796  }
797  }
798  case FrameStateData::Instr::kDematerializedObject: {
799  uint32_t obj_id;
800  uint32_t field_count;
801  it->ConsumeDematerializedObject(&obj_id, &field_count);
802  size_t id = deduplicator->GetObjectId(obj_id, ObjectType::kRegularObject);
803  if (id == TurboshaftStateObjectDeduplicator::kNotDuplicated) {
804  id = deduplicator->InsertObject(obj_id, ObjectType::kRegularObject);
805  size_t entries = 0;
806  StateValueList* nested = values->PushRecursiveField(zone, id);
807  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < field_count; ++i) {
808  entries += AddOperandToStateValueDescriptor(
809  selector, nested, inputs, g, deduplicator, it, kind, zone);
810  }
811  return entries;
812  } else {
813  // Deoptimizer counts duplicate objects for the running id, so we have
814  // to push the input again.
815  deduplicator->InsertObject(obj_id, ObjectType::kRegularObject);
816  values->PushDuplicate(id);
817  return 0;
818  }
819  }
820  case FrameStateData::Instr::kDematerializedObjectReference: {
821  uint32_t obj_id;
822  it->ConsumeDematerializedObjectReference(&obj_id);
823  size_t id = deduplicator->GetObjectId(obj_id, ObjectType::kRegularObject);
824  DCHECK_NE(id, TurboshaftStateObjectDeduplicator::kNotDuplicated);
825  // Deoptimizer counts duplicate objects for the running id, so we have
826  // to push the input again.
827  deduplicator->InsertObject(obj_id, ObjectType::kRegularObject);
828  values->PushDuplicate(id);
829  return 0;
830  }
831  case FrameStateData::Instr::kDematerializedStringConcat: {
832  DCHECK(v8_flags.turboshaft_string_concat_escape_analysis);
833  uint32_t obj_id;
834  it->ConsumeDematerializedStringConcat(&obj_id);
835  size_t id = deduplicator->GetObjectId(obj_id, ObjectType::kStringConcat);
836  if (id == TurboshaftStateObjectDeduplicator::kNotDuplicated) {
837  id = deduplicator->InsertObject(obj_id, ObjectType::kStringConcat);
838  StateValueList* nested = values->PushStringConcat(zone, id);
839  static constexpr int kLeft = 1, kRight = 1;
840  static constexpr int kInputCount = kLeft + kRight;
841  size_t entries = 0;
842  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < kInputCount; i++) {
843  entries += AddOperandToStateValueDescriptor(
844  selector, nested, inputs, g, deduplicator, it, kind, zone);
845  }
846  return entries;
847  } else {
848  // Deoptimizer counts duplicate objects for the running id, so we have
849  // to push the input again.
850  deduplicator->InsertObject(obj_id, ObjectType::kStringConcat);
851  values->PushDuplicate(id);
852  return 0;
853  }
854  }
855  case FrameStateData::Instr::kDematerializedStringConcatReference: {
856  DCHECK(v8_flags.turboshaft_string_concat_escape_analysis);
857  uint32_t obj_id;
858  it->ConsumeDematerializedStringConcatReference(&obj_id);
859  size_t id = deduplicator->GetObjectId(obj_id, ObjectType::kStringConcat);
860  DCHECK_NE(id, TurboshaftStateObjectDeduplicator::kNotDuplicated);
861  // Deoptimizer counts duplicate objects for the running id, so we have
862  // to push the input again.
863  deduplicator->InsertObject(obj_id, ObjectType::kStringConcat);
864  values->PushDuplicate(id);
865  return 0;
866  }
867  case FrameStateData::Instr::kArgumentsElements: {
868  CreateArgumentsType type;
869  it->ConsumeArgumentsElements(&type);
870  values->PushArgumentsElements(type);
871  // The elements backing store of an arguments object participates in the
872  // duplicate object counting, but can itself never appear duplicated.
873  deduplicator->InsertDummyForArgumentsElements();
874  return 0;
875  }
876  case FrameStateData::Instr::kArgumentsLength:
877  it->ConsumeArgumentsLength();
878  values->PushArgumentsLength();
879  return 0;
880  case FrameStateData::Instr::kRestLength:
881  it->ConsumeRestLength();
882  values->PushRestLength();
883  return 0;
884  }
885  UNREACHABLE();
886 }

888 // Returns the number of instruction operands added to inputs.
889 size_t InstructionSelector::AddInputsToFrameStateDescriptor(
890  FrameStateDescriptor* descriptor, OpIndex state_node, OperandGenerator* g,
891  TurboshaftStateObjectDeduplicator* deduplicator,
892  InstructionOperandVector* inputs, FrameStateInputKind kind, Zone* zone) {
893  FrameStateOp& state =
894  schedule()->Get(state_node).template Cast<FrameStateOp>();
895  const FrameStateInfo& info = state.data->frame_state_info;
896  USE(info);
897  FrameStateData::Iterator it = state.data->iterator(state.state_values());
898 
899  size_t entries = 0;
900  size_t initial_size = inputs->size();
901  USE(initial_size); // initial_size is only used for debug.
902  if (descriptor->outer_state()) {
903  entries += AddInputsToFrameStateDescriptor(
904  descriptor->outer_state(), state.parent_frame_state(), g, deduplicator,
905  inputs, kind, zone);
906  }
907 
908  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor->parameters_count(), info.parameter_count());
909  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor->locals_count(), info.local_count());
910  DCHECK_EQ(descriptor->stack_count(), info.stack_count());
911 
912  StateValueList* values_descriptor = descriptor->GetStateValueDescriptors();
913 
914  DCHECK_EQ(values_descriptor->size(), 0u);
915  values_descriptor->ReserveSize(descriptor->GetSize());
916 
917  // Function
918  if (descriptor->HasClosure()) {
919  entries += v8::internal::compiler::AddOperandToStateValueDescriptor(
920  this, values_descriptor, inputs, g, deduplicator, &it,
921  FrameStateInputKind::kStackSlot, zone);
922  } else {
923  // Advance the iterator either way.
924  MachineType unused_type;
925  OpIndex unused_input;
926  it.ConsumeInput(&unused_type, &unused_input);
927  }
928 
929  // Parameters
930  for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptor->parameters_count(); ++i) {
931  entries += v8::internal::compiler::AddOperandToStateValueDescriptor(
932  this, values_descriptor, inputs, g, deduplicator, &it, kind, zone);
933  }
934 
935  // Context
936  if (descriptor->HasContext()) {
937  entries += v8::internal::compiler::AddOperandToStateValueDescriptor(
938  this, values_descriptor, inputs, g, deduplicator, &it,
939  FrameStateInputKind::kStackSlot, zone);
940  } else {
941  // Advance the iterator either way.
942  MachineType unused_type;
943  OpIndex unused_input;
944  it.ConsumeInput(&unused_type, &unused_input);
945  }
946 
947  // Locals
948  for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptor->locals_count(); ++i) {
949  entries += v8::internal::compiler::AddOperandToStateValueDescriptor(
950  this, values_descriptor, inputs, g, deduplicator, &it, kind, zone);
951  }
952 
953  // Stack
954  for (size_t i = 0; i < descriptor->stack_count(); ++i) {
955  entries += v8::internal::compiler::AddOperandToStateValueDescriptor(
956  this, values_descriptor, inputs, g, deduplicator, &it, kind, zone);
957  }
958 
959  DCHECK_EQ(initial_size + entries, inputs->size());
960  return entries;
961 }

991 Instruction* InstructionSelector::EmitWithContinuation(
992  InstructionCode opcode, size_t output_count, InstructionOperand* outputs,
993  size_t input_count, InstructionOperand* inputs, size_t temp_count,
994  InstructionOperand* temps, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
995  OperandGenerator g(this);
996 
997  opcode = cont->Encode(opcode);
998 
999  continuation_inputs_.resize(0);
1000  for (size_t i = 0; i < input_count; i++) {
1001  continuation_inputs_.push_back(inputs[i]);
1002  }
1003 
1004  continuation_outputs_.resize(0);
1005  for (size_t i = 0; i < output_count; i++) {
1006  continuation_outputs_.push_back(outputs[i]);
1007  }
1008 
1009  continuation_temps_.resize(0);
1010  for (size_t i = 0; i < temp_count; i++) {
1011  continuation_temps_.push_back(temps[i]);
1012  }
1013 
1014  if (cont->IsBranch() || cont->IsConditionalBranch()) {
1015  continuation_inputs_.push_back(g.Label(cont->true_block()));
1016  continuation_inputs_.push_back(g.Label(cont->false_block()));
1017  } else if (cont->IsDeoptimize()) {
1018  int immediate_args_count = 0;
1019  opcode |= DeoptImmedArgsCountField::encode(immediate_args_count) |
1020  DeoptFrameStateOffsetField::encode(static_cast<int>(input_count));
1021  AppendDeoptimizeArguments(&continuation_inputs_, cont->reason(),
1022  cont->node_id(), cont->feedback(),
1023  cont->frame_state());
1024  } else if (cont->IsSet() || cont->IsConditionalSet()) {
1025  continuation_outputs_.push_back(g.DefineAsRegister(cont->result()));
1026  } else if (cont->IsSelect()) {
1027  // The {Select} should put one of two values into the output register,
1028  // depending on the result of the condition. The two result values are in
1029  // the last two input slots, the {false_value} in {input_count - 2}, and the
1030  // true_value in {input_count - 1}. The other inputs are used for the
1031  // condition.
1032  AddOutputToSelectContinuation(&g, static_cast<int>(input_count) - 2,
1033  cont->result());
1034  } else if (cont->IsTrap()) {
1035  int trap_id = static_cast<int>(cont->trap_id());
1036  continuation_inputs_.push_back(g.UseImmediate(trap_id));
1037  } else {
1038  DCHECK(cont->IsNone());
1039  }
1040 
1041  size_t const emit_inputs_size = continuation_inputs_.size();
1042  auto* emit_inputs =
1043  emit_inputs_size ? &continuation_inputs_.front() : nullptr;
1044  size_t const emit_outputs_size = continuation_outputs_.size();
1045  auto* emit_outputs =
1046  emit_outputs_size ? &continuation_outputs_.front() : nullptr;
1047  size_t const emit_temps_size = continuation_temps_.size();
1048  auto* emit_temps = emit_temps_size ? &continuation_temps_.front() : nullptr;
1049  return Emit(opcode, emit_outputs_size, emit_outputs, emit_inputs_size,
1050  emit_inputs, emit_temps_size, emit_temps);
1051 }

1053 bool InstructionSelector::IsProtectedLoad(turboshaft::OpIndex node) const {
1054 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1055  if (Get(node).opcode == turboshaft::Opcode::kSimd128LoadTransform) {
1056  return true;
1057  }
1058 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
1059  if (Get(node).opcode == turboshaft::Opcode::kSimd256LoadTransform) {
1060  return true;
1061  }
1062 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
1063 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1064 
1065  if (!IsLoadOrLoadImmutable(node)) return false;
1066 
1067  bool traps_on_null;
1068  return LoadView(schedule_, node).is_protected(&traps_on_null);
1069 }

1071 void InstructionSelector::AppendDeoptimizeArguments(
1072  InstructionOperandVector* args, DeoptimizeReason reason, uint32_t node_id,
1073  FeedbackSource const& feedback, OpIndex frame_state, DeoptimizeKind kind) {
1074  OperandGenerator g(this);
1075  FrameStateDescriptor* const descriptor = GetFrameStateDescriptor(frame_state);
1076  int const state_id = sequence()->AddDeoptimizationEntry(
1077  descriptor, kind, reason, node_id, feedback);
1078  args->push_back(g.TempImmediate(state_id));
1079  StateObjectDeduplicator deduplicator(instruction_zone());
1080  AddInputsToFrameStateDescriptor(descriptor, frame_state, &g, &deduplicator,
1081  args, FrameStateInputKind::kAny,
1082  instruction_zone());
1083 }

1085 // An internal helper class for generating the operands to calls.
1086 // TODO(bmeurer): Get rid of the CallBuffer business and make
1087 // InstructionSelector::VisitCall platform independent instead.
1088 struct CallBuffer {
1089  CallBuffer(Zone* zone, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
1090  FrameStateDescriptor* frame_state)
1091  : descriptor(call_descriptor),
1092  frame_state_descriptor(frame_state),
1093  output_nodes(zone),
1094  outputs(zone),
1095  instruction_args(zone),
1096  pushed_nodes(zone) {
1097  output_nodes.reserve(call_descriptor->ReturnCount());
1098  outputs.reserve(call_descriptor->ReturnCount());
1099  pushed_nodes.reserve(input_count());
1100  instruction_args.reserve(input_count() + frame_state_value_count());
1101  }
1102 
1103  const CallDescriptor* descriptor;
1104  FrameStateDescriptor* frame_state_descriptor;
1105  ZoneVector<PushParameter> output_nodes;
1106  InstructionOperandVector outputs;
1107  InstructionOperandVector instruction_args;
1108  ZoneVector<PushParameter> pushed_nodes;
1109 
1110  size_t input_count() const { return descriptor->InputCount(); }
1111 
1112  size_t frame_state_count() const { return descriptor->FrameStateCount(); }
1113 
1114  size_t frame_state_value_count() const {
1115  return (frame_state_descriptor == nullptr)
1116  ? 0
1117  : (frame_state_descriptor->GetTotalSize() +
1118  1); // Include deopt id.
1119  }
1120 };

1122 // TODO(bmeurer): Get rid of the CallBuffer business and make
1123 // InstructionSelector::VisitCall platform independent instead.
1124 void InstructionSelector::InitializeCallBuffer(
1125  OpIndex node, CallBuffer* buffer, CallBufferFlags flags, OpIndex callee,
1126  OptionalOpIndex frame_state_opt, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
1127  int return_count, int stack_param_delta) {
1128  OperandGenerator g(this);
1129  size_t ret_count = buffer->descriptor->ReturnCount();
1130  bool is_tail_call = (flags & kCallTail) != 0;
1131  DCHECK_LE(return_count, ret_count);
1132 
1133  if (ret_count > 0) {
1134  // Collect the projections that represent multiple outputs from this call.
1135  if (ret_count == 1) {
1136  PushParameter result = {node, buffer->descriptor->GetReturnLocation(0)};
1137  buffer->output_nodes.push_back(result);
1138  } else {
1139  buffer->output_nodes.resize(ret_count);
1140  for (size_t i = 0; i < ret_count; ++i) {
1141  LinkageLocation location = buffer->descriptor->GetReturnLocation(i);
1142  buffer->output_nodes[i] = PushParameter({}, location);
1143  }
1144  for (OpIndex call_use : turboshaft_uses(node)) {
1145  const Operation& use_op = this->Get(call_use);
1146  if (use_op.Is<DidntThrowOp>()) {
1147  for (OpIndex use : turboshaft_uses(call_use)) {
1148  const ProjectionOp& projection = Cast<ProjectionOp>(use);
1149  size_t index = projection.index;
1150  DCHECK_LT(index, buffer->output_nodes.size());
1151  DCHECK(!buffer->output_nodes[index].node.valid());
1152  buffer->output_nodes[index].node = use;
1153  }
1154  } else {
1155  DCHECK(use_op.Is<CheckExceptionOp>());
1156  }
1157  }
1158  frame_->EnsureReturnSlots(
1159  static_cast<int>(buffer->descriptor->ReturnSlotCount()));
1160  }
1161 
1162  // Filter out the outputs that aren't live because no projection uses them.
1163  size_t outputs_needed_by_framestate =
1164  buffer->frame_state_descriptor == nullptr
1165  ? 0
1166  : buffer->frame_state_descriptor->state_combine()
1167  .ConsumedOutputCount();
1168  for (size_t i = 0; i < buffer->output_nodes.size(); i++) {
1169  bool output_is_live = buffer->output_nodes[i].node.valid() ||
1170  i < outputs_needed_by_framestate;
1171  if (output_is_live) {
1172  LinkageLocation location = buffer->output_nodes[i].location;
1173  MachineRepresentation rep = location.GetType().representation();
1174 
1175  OpIndex output = buffer->output_nodes[i].node;
1176  InstructionOperand op = !output.valid()
1177  ? g.TempLocation(location)
1178  : g.DefineAsLocation(output, location);
1179  MarkAsRepresentation(rep, op);
1180 
1181  if (!UnallocatedOperand::cast(op).HasFixedSlotPolicy()) {
1182  buffer->outputs.push_back(op);
1183  buffer->output_nodes[i].node = {};
1184  }
1185  }
1186  }
1187  }
1188 
1189  // The first argument is always the callee code.
1190  bool call_code_immediate = (flags & kCallCodeImmediate) != 0;
1191  bool call_address_immediate = (flags & kCallAddressImmediate) != 0;
1192  bool call_use_fixed_target_reg = (flags & kCallFixedTargetRegister) != 0;
1193  DeoptimizeKind deopt_kind = DeoptimizeKind::kLazy;
1194  switch (buffer->descriptor->kind()) {
1195  case CallDescriptor::kCallCodeObject:
1196  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(
1197  (call_code_immediate && this->IsHeapConstant(callee))
1198  ? g.UseImmediate(callee)
1199  : call_use_fixed_target_reg
1200  ? g.UseFixed(callee, kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister)
1201  : g.UseRegister(callee));
1202  break;
1203  case CallDescriptor::kCallAddress:
1204  // TODO(ahaas): Rename kLazyAfterFastCall and similarly called fields on
1205  // the isolate to reflect that they are used for every direct call to C++
1206  // and not just for fast API calls.
1207  deopt_kind = DeoptimizeKind::kLazyAfterFastCall;
1208  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(
1209  (call_address_immediate && this->IsExternalConstant(callee))
1210  ? g.UseImmediate(callee)
1211  : call_use_fixed_target_reg
1212  ? g.UseFixed(callee, kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister)
1213  : g.UseRegister(callee));
1214  break;
1215 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1216  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmCapiFunction:
1217  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmFunction:
1218  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmFunctionIndirect:
1219  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmImportWrapper:
1220  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(
1221  (call_address_immediate && this->IsRelocatableWasmConstant(callee))
1222  ? g.UseImmediate(callee)
1223  : call_use_fixed_target_reg
1224  ? g.UseFixed(callee, kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister)
1225  : g.UseRegister(callee));
1226  break;
1227 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1228  case CallDescriptor::kCallBuiltinPointer: {
1229  // The common case for builtin pointers is to have the target in a
1230  // register. If we have a constant, we use a register anyway to simplify
1231  // related code.
1232  LinkageLocation location = buffer->descriptor->GetInputLocation(0);
1233  bool location_is_fixed_register =
1234  location.IsRegister() && !location.IsAnyRegister();
1235  InstructionOperand op;
1236  // If earlier phases specified a particular register, don't override
1237  // their choice.
1238  if (location_is_fixed_register) {
1239  op = g.UseLocation(callee, location);
1240  } else if (call_use_fixed_target_reg) {
1241  op = g.UseFixed(callee, kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
1242  } else {
1243  op = g.UseRegister(callee);
1244  }
1245  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(op);
1246  break;
1247  }
1248  case CallDescriptor::kCallJSFunction:
1249  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(
1250  g.UseLocation(callee, buffer->descriptor->GetInputLocation(0)));
1251  break;
1252  }
1253  DCHECK_EQ(1u, buffer->instruction_args.size());
1254 
1255  // If the call needs a frame state, we insert the state information as
1256  // follows (n is the number of value inputs to the frame state):
1257  // arg 1 : deoptimization id.
1258  // arg 2 - arg (n + 2) : value inputs to the frame state.
1259  size_t frame_state_entries = 0;
1260  USE(frame_state_entries); // frame_state_entries is only used for debug.
1261  if (buffer->frame_state_descriptor != nullptr) {
1262  OpIndex frame_state = frame_state_opt.value();
1263 
1264  // If it was a syntactic tail call we need to drop the current frame and
1265  // all the frames on top of it that are either inlined extra arguments
1266  // or a tail caller frame.
1267  if (is_tail_call) {
1268  frame_state = Cast<FrameStateOp>(frame_state).parent_frame_state();
1269  buffer->frame_state_descriptor =
1270  buffer->frame_state_descriptor->outer_state();
1271  while (buffer->frame_state_descriptor != nullptr &&
1272  buffer->frame_state_descriptor->type() ==
1273  FrameStateType::kInlinedExtraArguments) {
1274  frame_state = Cast<FrameStateOp>(frame_state).parent_frame_state();
1275  buffer->frame_state_descriptor =
1276  buffer->frame_state_descriptor->outer_state();
1277  }
1278  }
1279 
1280  int const state_id = sequence()->AddDeoptimizationEntry(
1281  buffer->frame_state_descriptor, deopt_kind, DeoptimizeReason::kUnknown,
1282  node.id(), FeedbackSource());
1283  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(g.TempImmediate(state_id));
1284 
1285  StateObjectDeduplicator deduplicator(instruction_zone());
1286 
1287  frame_state_entries =
1288  1 + AddInputsToFrameStateDescriptor(
1289  buffer->frame_state_descriptor, frame_state, &g, &deduplicator,
1290  &buffer->instruction_args, FrameStateInputKind::kStackSlot,
1291  instruction_zone());
1292 
1293  DCHECK_EQ(1 + frame_state_entries, buffer->instruction_args.size());
1294  }
1295 
1296  size_t input_count = buffer->input_count();
1297 
1298  // Split the arguments into pushed_nodes and instruction_args. Pushed
1299  // arguments require an explicit push instruction before the call and do
1300  // not appear as arguments to the call. Everything else ends up
1301  // as an InstructionOperand argument to the call.
1302  auto iter(arguments.begin());
1303  size_t pushed_count = 0;
1304  for (size_t index = 1; index < input_count; ++iter, ++index) {
1305  DCHECK_NE(iter, arguments.end());
1306 
1307  LinkageLocation location = buffer->descriptor->GetInputLocation(index);
1308  if (is_tail_call) {
1309  location = LinkageLocation::ConvertToTailCallerLocation(
1310  location, stack_param_delta);
1311  }
1312  InstructionOperand op = g.UseLocation(*iter, location);
1313  UnallocatedOperand unallocated = UnallocatedOperand::cast(op);
1314  if (unallocated.HasFixedSlotPolicy() && !is_tail_call) {
1315  int stack_index = buffer->descriptor->GetStackIndexFromSlot(
1316  unallocated.fixed_slot_index());
1317  // This can insert empty slots before stack_index and will insert enough
1318  // slots after stack_index to store the parameter.
1319  if (static_cast<size_t>(stack_index) >= buffer->pushed_nodes.size()) {
1320  int num_slots = location.GetSizeInPointers();
1321  buffer->pushed_nodes.resize(stack_index + num_slots);
1322  }
1323  PushParameter param = {*iter, location};
1324  buffer->pushed_nodes[stack_index] = param;
1325  pushed_count++;
1326  } else {
1327  if (location.IsNullRegister()) {
1328  EmitMoveFPRToParam(&op, location);
1329  }
1330  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(op);
1331  }
1332  }
1333  DCHECK_EQ(input_count, buffer->instruction_args.size() + pushed_count -
1334  frame_state_entries);
1335  USE(pushed_count);
1336  if (V8_TARGET_ARCH_STORES_RETURN_ADDRESS_ON_STACK && is_tail_call &&
1337  stack_param_delta != 0) {
1338  // For tail calls that change the size of their parameter list and keep
1339  // their return address on the stack, move the return address to just above
1340  // the parameters.
1341  LinkageLocation saved_return_location =
1342  LinkageLocation::ForSavedCallerReturnAddress();
1343  InstructionOperand return_address =
1344  g.UsePointerLocation(LinkageLocation::ConvertToTailCallerLocation(
1345  saved_return_location, stack_param_delta),
1346  saved_return_location);
1347  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(return_address);
1348  }
1349 }

1356 bool InstructionSelector::IsSourcePositionUsed(OpIndex node) {
1357  if (source_position_mode_ == InstructionSelector::kAllSourcePositions) {
1358  return true;
1359  }
1360  const Operation& operation = this->Get(node);
1361  // DidntThrow is where the actual call is generated.
1362  if (operation.Is<DidntThrowOp>()) return true;
1363  if (const LoadOp* load = operation.TryCast<LoadOp>()) {
1364  return load->kind.with_trap_handler;
1365  }
1366  if (const StoreOp* store = operation.TryCast<StoreOp>()) {
1367  return store->kind.with_trap_handler;
1368  }
1369 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1370  if (operation.Is<TrapIfOp>()) return true;
1371  if (const AtomicRMWOp* rmw = operation.TryCast<AtomicRMWOp>()) {
1372  return rmw->memory_access_kind ==
1373  MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler;
1374  }
1375  if (const Simd128LoadTransformOp* lt =
1376  operation.TryCast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>()) {
1377  return lt->load_kind.with_trap_handler;
1378  }
1379 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
1380  if (const Simd256LoadTransformOp* lt =
1381  operation.TryCast<Simd256LoadTransformOp>()) {
1382  return lt->load_kind.with_trap_handler;
1383  }
1384 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
1385  if (const Simd128LaneMemoryOp* lm =
1386  operation.TryCast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>()) {
1387  return lm->kind.with_trap_handler;
1388  }
1389 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_DEINTERLEAVED_MEM_OPS
1390  if (const Simd128LoadPairDeinterleaveOp* dl =
1391  operation.TryCast<Simd128LoadPairDeinterleaveOp>()) {
1392  return dl->load_kind.with_trap_handler;
1393  }
1394 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_DEINTERLEAVED_MEM_OPS
1395 #endif
1396  if (additional_protected_instructions_->Contains(node.id())) {
1397  return true;
1398  }
1399  return false;
1400 }

1402 bool InstructionSelector::IsCommutative(turboshaft::OpIndex node) const {
1403  const turboshaft::Operation& op = Get(node);
1404  if (const auto word_binop = op.TryCast<turboshaft::WordBinopOp>()) {
1405  return turboshaft::WordBinopOp::IsCommutative(word_binop->kind);
1406  } else if (const auto overflow_binop =
1407  op.TryCast<turboshaft::OverflowCheckedBinopOp>()) {
1408  return turboshaft::OverflowCheckedBinopOp::IsCommutative(
1409  overflow_binop->kind);
1410  } else if (const auto float_binop = op.TryCast<turboshaft::FloatBinopOp>()) {
1411  return !ensure_deterministic_nan_ &&
1412  turboshaft::FloatBinopOp::IsCommutative(float_binop->kind);
1413  } else if (const auto comparison = op.TryCast<turboshaft::ComparisonOp>()) {
1414  return turboshaft::ComparisonOp::IsCommutative(comparison->kind);
1415  }
1416  return false;
1417 }
1418 namespace {
1419 bool increment_effect_level_for_node(InstructionSelector* selector,
1420  OpIndex node) {
1421  // We need to increment the effect level if the operation consumes any of the
1422  // dimensions of the {kTurboshaftEffectLevelMask}.
1423  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
1424  if (op.Is<RetainOp>()) {
1425  // Retain has CanWrite effect so that it's not reordered before the last
1426  // read it protects, but it shouldn't increment the effect level, since
1427  // doing a Load(x) after a Retain(x) is safe as long as there is not call
1428  // (or something that can trigger GC) in between Retain(x) and Load(x), and
1429  // if there were, then this call would increment the effect level, which
1430  // would prevent covering in the ISEL.
1431  return false;
1432  }
1433  return (op.Effects().consumes.bits() & kTurboshaftEffectLevelMask.bits()) !=
1434  0;
1435 }
1436 } // namespace
1437 
1438 void InstructionSelector::VisitBlock(const Block* block) {
1439  DCHECK(!current_block_);
1440  current_block_ = block;
1441  auto current_num_instructions = [&] {
1442  DCHECK_GE(kMaxInt, instructions_.size());
1443  return static_cast<int>(instructions_.size());
1444  };
1445  int current_block_end = current_num_instructions();
1446 
1447  int effect_level = 0;
1448  for (OpIndex node : this->nodes(block)) {
1449  SetEffectLevel(node, effect_level);
1450  if (increment_effect_level_for_node(this, node)) {
1451  ++effect_level;
1452  }
1453  }
1454 
1455  // We visit the control first, then the nodes in the block, so the block's
1456  // control input should be on the same effect level as the last node.
1457  if (OpIndex terminator = this->block_terminator(block); terminator.valid()) {
1458  SetEffectLevel(terminator, effect_level);
1459  current_effect_level_ = effect_level;
1460  }
1461 
1462  auto FinishEmittedInstructions = [&](OpIndex node, int instruction_start) {
1463  if (instruction_selection_failed()) return false;
1464  if (current_num_instructions() == instruction_start) return true;
1465  std::reverse(instructions_.begin() + instruction_start,
1466  instructions_.end());
1467  if (!node.valid()) return true;
1468  if (!source_positions_) return true;
1469 
1470  SourcePosition source_position;
1471 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY && V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
1472  if (const Simd128UnaryOp* op =
1473  TryCast<Opmask::kSimd128F64x2PromoteLowF32x4>(node);
1474  V8_UNLIKELY(op)) {
1475  // On x64 there exists an optimization that folds
1476  // `kF64x2PromoteLowF32x4` and `kS128Load64Zero` together into a single
1477  // instruction. If the instruction causes an out-of-bounds memory
1478  // access exception, then the stack trace has to show the source
1479  // position of the `kS128Load64Zero` and not of the
1480  // `kF64x2PromoteLowF32x4`.
1481  if (CanOptimizeF64x2PromoteLowF32x4(node)) {
1482  node = op->input();
1483  }
1484  }
1485 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY && V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
1486  source_position = (*source_positions_)[node];
1487  if (source_position.IsKnown() && IsSourcePositionUsed(node)) {
1488  sequence()->SetSourcePosition(instructions_.back(), source_position);
1489  }
1490  return true;
1491  };
1492 
1493  // Generate code for the block control "top down", but schedule the code
1494  // "bottom up".
1495  VisitControl(block);
1496  if (!FinishEmittedInstructions(this->block_terminator(block),
1497  current_block_end)) {
1498  return;
1499  }
1500 
1501  // Visit code in reverse control flow order, because architecture-specific
1502  // matching may cover more than one node at a time.
1503  for (OpIndex node : base::Reversed(this->nodes(block))) {
1504  int current_node_end = current_num_instructions();
1505 
1506  if (protected_loads_to_remove_->Contains(node.id()) &&
1507  !IsReallyUsed(node)) {
1508  MarkAsDefined(node);
1509  }
1510 
1511  if (!IsUsed(node)) {
1512  // Skip nodes that are unused, while marking them as Defined so that it's
1513  // clear that these unused nodes have been visited and will not be Defined
1514  // later.
1515  MarkAsDefined(node);
1516  } else if (!IsDefined(node)) {
1517  // Generate code for this node "top down", but schedule the code "bottom
1518  // up".
1519  current_effect_level_ = GetEffectLevel(node);
1520  VisitNode(node);
1521  if (!FinishEmittedInstructions(node, current_node_end)) return;
1522  }
1523  if (trace_turbo_) {
1524  instr_origins_[node.id()] = {current_num_instructions(),
1525  current_node_end};
1526  }
1527  }
1528 
1529  // We're done with the block.
1530  InstructionBlock* instruction_block =
1531  sequence()->InstructionBlockAt(this->rpo_number(block));
1532  if (current_num_instructions() == current_block_end) {
1533  // Avoid empty block: insert a {kArchNop} instruction.
1534  Emit(Instruction::New(sequence()->zone(), kArchNop));
1535  }
1536  instruction_block->set_code_start(current_num_instructions());
1537  instruction_block->set_code_end(current_block_end);
1538  current_block_ = nullptr;
1539 }

1568 void InstructionSelector::ConsumeEqualZero(OpIndex* user, OpIndex* value,
1569  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
1570  // Try to combine with comparisons against 0 by simply inverting the branch.
1571  while (const ComparisonOp* equal =
1572  TryCast<Opmask::kComparisonEqual>(*value)) {
1573  if (equal->rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32()) {
1574  if (!MatchIntegralZero(equal->right())) return;
1575 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1576  } else if (equal->rep == RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()) {
1577  static_assert(RegisterRepresentation::Tagged().MapTaggedToWord() ==
1578  RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
1579  if (!MatchSmiZero(equal->right())) return;
1580 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1581  } else {
1582  return;
1583  }
1584  if (!CanCover(*user, *value)) return;
1585 
1586  *user = *value;
1587  *value = equal->left();
1588  cont->Negate();
1589  }
1590 }

1722 void InstructionSelector::EmitTableSwitch(
1723  const SwitchInfo& sw, InstructionOperand const& index_operand) {
1724  OperandGenerator g(this);
1725  size_t input_count = 2 + sw.value_range();
1726  DCHECK_LE(sw.value_range(), std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max() - 2);
1727  auto* inputs =
1728  zone()->template AllocateArray<InstructionOperand>(input_count);
1729  inputs[0] = index_operand;
1730  InstructionOperand default_operand = g.Label(sw.default_branch());
1731  std::fill(&inputs[1], &inputs[input_count], default_operand);
1732  for (const CaseInfo& c : sw.CasesUnsorted()) {
1733  size_t value = c.value - sw.min_value();
1734  DCHECK_LE(0u, value);
1735  DCHECK_LT(value + 2, input_count);
1736  inputs[value + 2] = g.Label(c.branch);
1737  MarkAsTableSwitchTarget(c.branch);
1738  }
1739  // If the default operand still exists in the cases, to fill gaps, then we
1740  // need to mark the default block as table switch target.
1741  if (std::find(&inputs[2], &inputs[input_count], default_operand) !=
1742  &inputs[input_count]) {
1743  MarkAsTableSwitchTarget(sw.default_branch());
1744  }
1745  Emit(kArchTableSwitch, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs, 0, nullptr);
1746 }
1747 
1748 void InstructionSelector::EmitBinarySearchSwitch(
1749  const SwitchInfo& sw, InstructionOperand const& value_operand) {
1750  OperandGenerator g(this);
1751  size_t input_count = 2 + sw.case_count() * 2;
1752  DCHECK_LE(sw.case_count(), (std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max() - 2) / 2);
1753  auto* inputs =
1754  zone()->template AllocateArray<InstructionOperand>(input_count);
1755  inputs[0] = value_operand;
1756  inputs[1] = g.Label(sw.default_branch());
1757  std::vector<CaseInfo> cases = sw.CasesSortedByValue();
1758  for (size_t index = 0; index < cases.size(); ++index) {
1759  const CaseInfo& c = cases[index];
1760  inputs[index * 2 + 2 + 0] = g.TempImmediate(c.value);
1761  inputs[index * 2 + 2 + 1] = g.Label(c.branch);
1762  }
1763  Emit(kArchBinarySearchSwitch, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs, 0, nullptr);
1764 }

1776 void InstructionSelector::VisitBitcastSmiToWord(OpIndex node) {
1777  // TODO(dmercadier): using EmitIdentity here is not ideal, because users of
1778  // {node} will then use its input, which may not have the Word32
1779  // representation. This might in turn lead to the register allocator wrongly
1780  // tracking Tagged values that are in fact just Smis. However, using
1781  // Emit(kArchNop) hurts performance because it inserts a gap move which cannot
1782  // always be eliminated because the operands may have different sizes (and the
1783  // move is then truncating or extending). As a temporary work-around until the
1784  // register allocator is fixed, we use Emit(kArchNop) in DEBUG mode to silence
1785  // the register allocator verifier.

1787  // registers.
1788 #if defined(DEBUG) || defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_LOONG64)
1789  OperandGenerator g(this);
1790  Emit(kArchNop, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
1791  g.Use(this->Get(node).Cast<TaggedBitcastOp>().input()));

1793  EmitIdentity(node);
1794 #endif

2004 void InstructionSelector::VisitPhi(OpIndex node) {
2005  const Operation& op = Get(node);
2006  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, PredecessorCount(current_block_));
2007  PhiInstruction* phi = instruction_zone()->template New<PhiInstruction>(
2008  instruction_zone(), GetVirtualRegister(node),
2009  static_cast<size_t>(op.input_count));
2010  sequence()->InstructionBlockAt(rpo_number(current_block_))->AddPhi(phi);
2011  for (size_t i = 0; i < op.input_count; ++i) {
2012  OpIndex input = op.input(i);
2013  MarkAsUsed(input);
2014  phi->SetInput(i, GetVirtualRegister(input));
2015  }
2016 }

2018 void InstructionSelector::VisitProjection(OpIndex node) {
2019  const ProjectionOp& projection = this->Get(node).Cast<ProjectionOp>();
2020  const Operation& value_op = this->Get(projection.input());
2021  if (value_op.Is<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>() ||
2022  value_op.Is<OverflowCheckedUnaryOp>() || value_op.Is<TryChangeOp>() ||
2023  value_op.Is<Word32PairBinopOp>()) {
2024  if (projection.index == 0u) {
2025  EmitIdentity(node);
2026  } else {
2027  DCHECK_EQ(1u, projection.index);
2028  MarkAsUsed(projection.input());
2029  }
2030  } else if (value_op.Is<DidntThrowOp>()) {
2031  // Nothing to do here?
2032  } else if (value_op.Is<CallOp>()) {
2033  // Call projections need to be behind the call's DidntThrow.
2034  UNREACHABLE();
2035  } else if (value_op.Is<AtomicWord32PairOp>()) {
2036  // Nothing to do here.
2037 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_DEINTERLEAVED_MEM_OPS
2038  } else if (value_op.Is<Simd128LoadPairDeinterleaveOp>()) {
2039  MarkAsUsed(projection.input());
2040 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_DEINTERLEAVED_MEM_OPS
2041  } else {
2042  UNIMPLEMENTED();
2043  }
2044 }

2046 bool InstructionSelector::CanDoBranchIfOverflowFusion(OpIndex binop) {
2047  const Graph* graph = this->turboshaft_graph();
2048  DCHECK(graph->Get(binop).template Is<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>() ||
2049  graph->Get(binop).template Is<OverflowCheckedUnaryOp>());
2050 
2051  // Getting the 1st projection. Projections are always emitted right after the
2052  // operation, in ascending order.
2053  OpIndex projection0_index = graph->NextIndex(binop);
2054  const ProjectionOp& projection0 =
2055  graph->Get(projection0_index).Cast<ProjectionOp>();
2056  DCHECK_EQ(projection0.index, 0);
2057 
2058  if (IsDefined(projection0_index)) {
2059  // In Turboshaft, this can only happen if {projection0_index} has already
2060  // been eagerly scheduled somewhere else, like in
2061  // TryPrepareScheduleFirstProjection.
2062  return true;
2063  }
2064 
2065  if (projection0.saturated_use_count.IsOne()) {
2066  // If the projection has a single use, it is the following tuple, so we
2067  // don't care about the value, and can do branch-if-overflow fusion.
2068  DCHECK(turboshaft_uses(projection0_index).size() == 1 &&
2069  graph->Get(turboshaft_uses(projection0_index)[0]).Is<TupleOp>());
2070  return true;
2071  }
2072 
2073  if (this->block(schedule_, binop) != current_block_) {
2074  // {binop} is not supposed to be defined in the current block, so let's not
2075  // pull it in this block (the checks would need to be stronger, and it's
2076  // unlikely that it's doable because of effect levels and all).
2077  return false;
2078  }
2079 
2080  // We now need to make sure that all uses of {projection0} are already
2081  // defined, which will imply that it's fine to define {projection0} and
2082  // {binop} now.
2083  for (OpIndex use : turboshaft_uses(projection0_index)) {
2084  if (this->Get(use).template Is<TupleOp>()) {
2085  // The Tuple won't have any uses since it would have to be accessed
2086  // through Projections, and Projections on Tuples return the original
2087  // Projection instead (see Assembler::ReduceProjection in
2088  // turboshaft/assembler.h).
2089  DCHECK(this->Get(use).saturated_use_count.IsZero());
2090  continue;
2091  }
2092  if (IsDefined(use)) continue;
2093  if (this->block(schedule_, use) != current_block_) {
2094  // {use} is in a later block, so it should already have been visited. Note
2095  // that operations that don't produce values are not marked as Defined,
2096  // like Return for instance, so it's possible that {use} has been visited
2097  // but the previous `IsDefined` check didn't match.
2098 
2099 #ifdef DEBUG
2100  if (this->block(schedule_, use)->index() < current_block_->index()) {
2101  // If {use} is in a previous block, then it has to be a loop Phi that
2102  // uses {projection0} as its backedge input. In that case, it's fine to
2103  // schedule the binop right now, even though it's after the use of its
2104  // 1st projection (since the use is conceptually after rather than
2105  // before because it goes through a backedge).
2106  DCHECK(this->Get(use).template Is<PhiOp>());
2107  DCHECK_EQ(this->Get(use).template Cast<PhiOp>().input(1),
2108  projection0_index);
2109  }
2110 #endif
2111 
2112  continue;
2113  }
2114 
2115  if (this->Get(use).template Is<PhiOp>()) {
2116  DCHECK_EQ(this->block(schedule_, use), current_block_);
2117  // If {projection0} is used by a Phi in the current block, then it has to
2118  // be a loop phi, and {projection0} has to be its backedge value. This
2119  // doesn't prevent scheduling {projection0} now, since anyways it
2120  // necessarily needs to be scheduled after the Phi.
2121  DCHECK(current_block_->IsLoop());
2122  continue;
2123  }
2124 
2125  // {use} is not defined yet (and is not a special case), which means that
2126  // {projection0} has a use that comes before {binop}, and we thus can't fuse
2127  // binop with a branch to do a branch-if-overflow.
2128  return false;
2129  }
2130 
2131  VisitProjection(projection0_index);
2132  return true;
2133 }

2146 void InstructionSelector::VisitCall(OpIndex node, Block* handler) {
2147  OperandGenerator g(this);
2148  const CallOp& call_op = Cast<CallOp>(node);
2149  const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = call_op.descriptor->descriptor;
2150  SaveFPRegsMode mode = call_descriptor->NeedsCallerSavedFPRegisters()
2151  ? SaveFPRegsMode::kSave
2152  : SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore;
2153 
2154  if (call_descriptor->NeedsCallerSavedRegisters()) {
2155  Emit(kArchSaveCallerRegisters | MiscField::encode(static_cast<int>(mode)),
2156  g.NoOutput());
2157  }
2158 
2159  FrameStateDescriptor* frame_state_descriptor = nullptr;
2160  if (call_descriptor->NeedsFrameState()) {
2161  frame_state_descriptor =
2162  GetFrameStateDescriptor(call_op.frame_state().value());
2163  }
2164 
2165  CallBuffer buffer(zone(), call_descriptor, frame_state_descriptor);
2166  CallDescriptor::Flags flags = call_descriptor->flags();
2167 
2168  // Compute InstructionOperands for inputs and outputs.
2169  // TODO(turbofan): on some architectures it's probably better to use
2170  // the code object in a register if there are multiple uses of it.
2171  // Improve constant pool and the heuristics in the register allocator
2172  // for where to emit constants.
2173  CallBufferFlags call_buffer_flags(kCallCodeImmediate | kCallAddressImmediate);
2174  if (flags & CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister) {
2175  call_buffer_flags |= kCallFixedTargetRegister;
2176  }
2177  InitializeCallBuffer(node, &buffer, call_buffer_flags, call_op.callee(),
2178  call_op.frame_state(), call_op.arguments(),
2179  static_cast<int>(call_op.results_rep().size()));
2180 
2181  EmitPrepareArguments(&buffer.pushed_nodes, call_descriptor, node);
2182  UpdateMaxPushedArgumentCount(buffer.pushed_nodes.size());
2183 
2184  InstructionOperandVector temps(zone());
2185 
2186 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2187  if (call_descriptor->IsIndirectWasmFunctionCall()) {
2188  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(
2189  g.UseImmediate64(call_descriptor->signature_hash()));
2190  }
2191 #endif
2192 
2193  if (call_descriptor->RequiresEntrypointTagForCall()) {
2194  DCHECK(!call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall());
2195  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(
2196  g.TempImmediate(call_descriptor->shifted_tag()));
2197  } else if (call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall()) {
2198  // For JSFunctions we need to know the number of pushed parameters during
2199  // code generation.
2200  uint32_t parameter_count =
2201  static_cast<uint32_t>(buffer.pushed_nodes.size());
2202  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(g.TempImmediate(parameter_count));
2203  }
2204 
2205  // Pass label of exception handler block.
2206  if (handler) {
2207  flags |= CallDescriptor::kHasExceptionHandler;
2208  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(g.Label(handler));
2209  } else {
2210  if (call_op.descriptor->lazy_deopt_on_throw == LazyDeoptOnThrow::kYes) {
2211  flags |= CallDescriptor::kHasExceptionHandler;
2212  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(
2213  g.UseImmediate(kLazyDeoptOnThrowSentinel));
2214  }
2215  }
2216 
2217  // Select the appropriate opcode based on the call type.
2218  InstructionCode opcode;
2219  switch (call_descriptor->kind()) {
2220  case CallDescriptor::kCallAddress: {
2221  int gp_param_count =
2222  static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->GPParameterCount());
2223  int fp_param_count =
2224  static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->FPParameterCount());
2225 #if ABI_USES_FUNCTION_DESCRIPTORS
2226  // Highest fp_param_count bit is used on AIX to indicate if a CFunction
2227  // call has function descriptor or not.
2228  static_assert(FPParamField::kSize == kHasFunctionDescriptorBitShift + 1);
2229  if (!call_descriptor->NoFunctionDescriptor()) {
2230  fp_param_count |= 1 << kHasFunctionDescriptorBitShift;
2231  }
2232 #endif
2233  // We store the param counts as a separate input because they need too
2234  // many bits to be encoded in the opcode.
2235  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(
2236  g.UseImmediate(ParamField::encode(gp_param_count) |
2237  FPParamField::encode(fp_param_count)));
2238  opcode = EncodeCallDescriptorFlags(kArchCallCFunction, flags);
2239  break;
2240  }
2241  case CallDescriptor::kCallCodeObject:
2242  opcode = EncodeCallDescriptorFlags(kArchCallCodeObject, flags);
2243  break;
2244  case CallDescriptor::kCallJSFunction:
2245  opcode = EncodeCallDescriptorFlags(kArchCallJSFunction, flags);
2246  break;
2247 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2248  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmCapiFunction:
2249  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmFunction:
2250  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmImportWrapper:
2251  DCHECK(this->IsRelocatableWasmConstant(call_op.callee()));
2252  opcode = EncodeCallDescriptorFlags(kArchCallWasmFunction, flags);
2253  break;
2254  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmFunctionIndirect:
2255  DCHECK(!this->IsRelocatableWasmConstant(call_op.callee()));
2256  opcode = EncodeCallDescriptorFlags(kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect, flags);
2257  break;
2258 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2259  case CallDescriptor::kCallBuiltinPointer:
2260  opcode = EncodeCallDescriptorFlags(kArchCallBuiltinPointer, flags);
2261  break;
2262  }
2263 
2264  // Emit the call instruction.
2265  size_t const output_count = buffer.outputs.size();
2266  auto* outputs = output_count ? &buffer.outputs.front() : nullptr;
2267  Instruction* call_instr =
2268  Emit(opcode, output_count, outputs, buffer.instruction_args.size(),
2269  &buffer.instruction_args.front());
2270  if (instruction_selection_failed()) return;
2271  call_instr->MarkAsCall();
2272 
2273  EmitPrepareResults(&(buffer.output_nodes), call_descriptor, node);
2274 
2275  if (call_descriptor->NeedsCallerSavedRegisters()) {
2276  Emit(
2277  kArchRestoreCallerRegisters | MiscField::encode(static_cast<int>(mode)),
2278  g.NoOutput());
2279  }
2280 }

2282 void InstructionSelector::VisitTailCall(OpIndex node) {
2283  OperandGenerator g(this);
2284 
2285  const TailCallOp& call_op = Cast<TailCallOp>(node);
2286  auto caller = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
2287  auto callee = call_op.descriptor->descriptor;
2288  DCHECK(caller->CanTailCall(callee));
2289  const int stack_param_delta = callee->GetStackParameterDelta(caller);
2290  CallBuffer buffer(zone(), callee, nullptr);
2291 
2292  // Compute InstructionOperands for inputs and outputs.
2293  CallBufferFlags flags(kCallCodeImmediate | kCallTail);
2294  if (IsTailCallAddressImmediate()) {
2295  flags |= kCallAddressImmediate;
2296  }
2297  if (callee->flags() & CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister) {
2298  flags |= kCallFixedTargetRegister;
2299  }
2300  InitializeCallBuffer(node, &buffer, flags, call_op.callee(),
2301  OptionalOpIndex::Nullopt(), call_op.arguments(),
2302  static_cast<int>(call_op.outputs_rep().size()),
2303  stack_param_delta);
2304  UpdateMaxPushedArgumentCount(stack_param_delta);
2305 
2306  // Select the appropriate opcode based on the call type.
2307  InstructionCode opcode;
2308  InstructionOperandVector temps(zone());
2309  switch (callee->kind()) {
2310  case CallDescriptor::kCallCodeObject:
2311  opcode = kArchTailCallCodeObject;
2312  break;
2313  case CallDescriptor::kCallAddress:
2314  DCHECK(!caller->IsJSFunctionCall());
2315  opcode = kArchTailCallAddress;
2316  break;
2317 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2318  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmFunction:
2319  DCHECK(!caller->IsJSFunctionCall());
2320  DCHECK(this->IsRelocatableWasmConstant(call_op.callee()));
2321  opcode = kArchTailCallWasm;
2322  break;
2323  case CallDescriptor::kCallWasmFunctionIndirect:
2324  DCHECK(!caller->IsJSFunctionCall());
2325  DCHECK(!this->IsRelocatableWasmConstant(call_op.callee()));
2326  opcode = kArchTailCallWasmIndirect;
2327  break;
2328 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2329  default:
2330  UNREACHABLE();
2331  }
2332  opcode = EncodeCallDescriptorFlags(opcode, callee->flags());
2333 
2334  Emit(kArchPrepareTailCall, g.NoOutput());
2335 
2336 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2337  if (callee->IsIndirectWasmFunctionCall()) {
2338  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(
2339  g.UseImmediate64(callee->signature_hash()));
2340  }
2341 #endif
2342 
2343  if (callee->RequiresEntrypointTagForCall()) {
2344  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(g.TempImmediate(callee->shifted_tag()));
2345  }
2346 
2347  // Add an immediate operand that represents the offset to the first slot
2348  // that is unused with respect to the stack pointer that has been updated
2349  // for the tail call instruction. Backends that pad arguments can write the
2350  // padding value at this offset from the stack.
2351  const int optional_padding_offset =
2352  callee->GetOffsetToFirstUnusedStackSlot() - 1;
2353  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(g.TempImmediate(optional_padding_offset));
2354 
2355  const int first_unused_slot_offset =
2356  kReturnAddressStackSlotCount + stack_param_delta;
2357  buffer.instruction_args.push_back(g.TempImmediate(first_unused_slot_offset));
2358 
2359  // Emit the tailcall instruction.
2360  Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, buffer.instruction_args.size(),
2361  &buffer.instruction_args.front(), temps.size(),
2362  temps.empty() ? nullptr : &temps.front());
2363 }

2371 void InstructionSelector::VisitReturn(OpIndex node) {
2372  const ReturnOp& ret = schedule()->Get(node).Cast<ReturnOp>();
2373 
2374  OperandGenerator g(this);
2375  const size_t return_count = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor()->ReturnCount();
2376  const int input_count =
2377  return_count == 0 ? 1
2378  : (1 + static_cast<int>(ret.return_values().size()));
2379  DCHECK_GE(input_count, 1);
2380 
2381  auto value_locations =
2382  zone()->template AllocateArray<InstructionOperand>(input_count);
2383  const Operation& pop_count = schedule()->Get(ret.pop_count());
2384  if (pop_count.Is<Opmask::kWord32Constant>() ||
2385  pop_count.Is<Opmask::kWord64Constant>()) {
2386  value_locations[0] = g.UseImmediate(ret.pop_count());
2387  } else {
2388  value_locations[0] = g.UseRegister(ret.pop_count());
2389  }
2390  for (size_t i = 0, return_value_idx = 0; i < return_count; ++i) {
2391  LinkageLocation loc = linkage()->GetReturnLocation(i);
2392  // Return values passed via frame slots have already been stored
2393  // on the stack by the GrowableStacksReducer.
2394  if (loc.IsCallerFrameSlot() && ret.spill_caller_frame_slots) {
2395  continue;
2396  }
2397  value_locations[return_value_idx + 1] =
2398  g.UseLocation(ret.return_values()[return_value_idx], loc);
2399  return_value_idx++;
2400  }
2401  Emit(kArchRet, 0, nullptr, input_count, value_locations);
2402 }

2404 void InstructionSelector::VisitBranch(OpIndex branch_node, Block* tbranch,
2405  Block* fbranch) {
2406  const BranchOp& branch = Cast<BranchOp>(branch_node);
2407  TryPrepareScheduleFirstProjection(branch.condition());
2408 
2409 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2410  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForHintedBranch(
2411  kNotEqual, tbranch, fbranch, branch.hint);
2412 #else
2413  FlagsContinuation cont =
2414  FlagsContinuation::ForBranch(kNotEqual, tbranch, fbranch);
2415 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2416  VisitWordCompareZero(branch_node, branch.condition(), &cont);
2417 }
2418 
2419 // When a DeoptimizeIf/DeoptimizeUnless/Branch depends on a BinopOverflow, the
2420 // InstructionSelector can sometimes generate a fuse instruction covering both
2421 // the BinopOverflow and the DeoptIf/Branch, and the final emitted code will
2422 // look like:
2423 //
2424 // r = BinopOverflow
2425 // jo branch_target/deopt_target
2426 //
2427 // When this fusing fails, the final code looks like:
2428 //
2429 // r = BinopOverflow
2430 // o = sete // sets overflow bit
2431 // cmp o, 0
2432 // jnz branch_target/deopt_target
2433 //
2434 // To be able to fuse tue BinopOverflow and the DeoptIf/Branch, the 1st
2435 // projection (Projection[0], which contains the actual result) must already be
2436 // scheduled (and a few other conditions must be satisfied, see
2437 // InstructionSelectorXXX::VisitWordCompareZero).
2438 // TryPrepareScheduleFirstProjection is thus called from
2439 // VisitDeoptimizeIf/VisitBranch and detects if the 1st
2440 // projection could be scheduled now, and, if so, defines it.
2441 void InstructionSelector::TryPrepareScheduleFirstProjection(
2442  OpIndex maybe_projection) {
2443  // The DeoptimizeIf/Branch condition is not a projection.
2444  const ProjectionOp* projection = TryCast<ProjectionOp>(maybe_projection);
2445  if (!projection) return;
2446 
2447  if (projection->index != 1u) {
2448  // The DeoptimizeIf/Branch isn't on the Projection[1]
2449  // (ie, not on the overflow bit of a BinopOverflow).
2450  return;
2451  }
2452 
2453  DCHECK_EQ(projection->input_count, 1);
2454  OpIndex node = projection->input();
2455  if (block(schedule_, node) != current_block_) {
2456  // The projection input is not in the current block, so it shouldn't be
2457  // emitted now, so we don't need to eagerly schedule its Projection[0].
2458  return;
2459  }
2460 
2461  auto* binop = TryCast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>(node);
2462  auto* unop = TryCast<OverflowCheckedUnaryOp>(node);
2463  if (binop == nullptr && unop == nullptr) return;
2464  if (binop) {
2465  DCHECK(binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedAdd ||
2466  binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedSub ||
2467  binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMul);
2468  } else {
2469  DCHECK_EQ(unop->kind, OverflowCheckedUnaryOp::Kind::kAbs);
2470  }
2471 
2472  OptionalOpIndex result = FindProjection(node, 0);
2473  if (!result.valid() || IsDefined(result.value())) {
2474  // No Projection(0), or it's already defined.
2475  return;
2476  }
2477 
2478  if (block(schedule_, result.value()) != current_block_) {
2479  // {result} wasn't planned to be scheduled in {current_block_}. To
2480  // avoid adding checks to see if it can still be scheduled now, we
2481  // just bail out.
2482  return;
2483  }
2484 
2485  // Checking if all uses of {result} that are in the current block have
2486  // already been Defined.
2487  // We also ignore Phi uses: if {result} is used in a Phi in the block in
2488  // which it is defined, this means that this block is a loop header, and
2489  // {result} back into it through the back edge. In this case, it's
2490  // normal to schedule {result} before the Phi that uses it.
2491  for (OpIndex use : turboshaft_uses(result.value())) {
2492  // We ignore TupleOp uses, since TupleOp don't lead to emitted machine
2493  // instructions and are just Turboshaft "meta operations".
2494  if (!Is<TupleOp>(use) && !IsDefined(use) &&
2495  block(schedule_, use) == current_block_ && !Is<PhiOp>(use)) {
2496  return;
2497  }
2498  }
2499 
2500  // Visiting the projection now. Note that this relies on the fact that
2501  // VisitProjection doesn't Emit something: if it did, then we could be
2502  // Emitting something after a Branch, which is invalid (Branch can only
2503  // be at the end of a block, and the end of a block must always be a
2504  // block terminator). (remember that we emit operation in reverse order,
2505  // so because we are doing TryPrepareScheduleFirstProjection before
2506  // actually emitting the Branch, it would be after in the final
2507  // instruction sequence, not before)
2508  VisitProjection(result.value());
2509 }

2515

2518  deopt.parameters->feedback(), deopt.frame_state());

2603 void InstructionSelector::VisitControl(const Block* block) {
2604 #ifdef DEBUG
2605  // SSA deconstruction requires targets of branches not to have phis.
2606  // Edge split form guarantees this property, but is more strict.
2607  if (auto successors =
2608  SuccessorBlocks(block->LastOperation(*turboshaft_graph()));
2609  successors.size() > 1) {
2610  for (Block* successor : successors) {
2611  if (successor->HasPhis(*turboshaft_graph())) {
2612  std::ostringstream str;
2613  str << "You might have specified merged variables for a label with "
2614  << "only one predecessor." << std::endl
2615  << "# Current Block: " << successor->index() << std::endl;
2616  FATAL("%s", str.str().c_str());
2617  }
2618  }
2619  }
2620 #endif // DEBUG
2621  const Operation& op = block->LastOperation(*schedule());
2622  OpIndex node = schedule()->Index(op);
2623  int instruction_end = static_cast<int>(instructions_.size());
2624  switch (op.opcode) {
2625  case Opcode::kGoto:
2626  VisitGoto(op.Cast<GotoOp>().destination);
2627  break;
2628  case Opcode::kReturn:
2629  VisitReturn(node);
2630  break;
2631  case Opcode::kTailCall:
2632  VisitTailCall(node);
2633  break;
2634  case Opcode::kDeoptimize: {
2635  const DeoptimizeOp& deoptimize = op.Cast<DeoptimizeOp>();
2636  VisitDeoptimize(deoptimize.parameters->reason(), node.id(),
2637  deoptimize.parameters->feedback(),
2638  deoptimize.frame_state());
2639  break;
2640  }
2641  case Opcode::kBranch: {
2642  const BranchOp& branch = op.Cast<BranchOp>();
2643  Block* tbranch = branch.if_true;
2644  Block* fbranch = branch.if_false;
2645  if (tbranch == fbranch) {
2646  VisitGoto(tbranch);
2647  } else {
2648  VisitBranch(node, tbranch, fbranch);
2649  }
2650  break;
2651  }
2652  case Opcode::kSwitch: {
2653  const SwitchOp& swtch = op.Cast<SwitchOp>();
2654  int32_t min_value = std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max();
2655  int32_t max_value = std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
2656 
2657  ZoneVector<CaseInfo> cases(swtch.cases.size(), zone());
2658  for (size_t i = 0; i < swtch.cases.size(); ++i) {
2659  const SwitchOp::Case& c = swtch.cases[i];
2660  cases[i] = CaseInfo{c.value, 0, c.destination};
2661  if (min_value > c.value) min_value = c.value;
2662  if (max_value < c.value) max_value = c.value;
2663  }
2664  SwitchInfo sw(std::move(cases), min_value, max_value, swtch.default_case);
2665  return VisitSwitch(node, sw);
2666  }
2667  case Opcode::kCheckException: {
2668  const CheckExceptionOp& check = op.Cast<CheckExceptionOp>();
2669  VisitCall(check.throwing_operation(), check.catch_block);
2670  VisitGoto(check.didnt_throw_block);
2671  return;
2672  }
2673  case Opcode::kUnreachable:
2674  return VisitUnreachable(node);
2675  case Opcode::kStaticAssert:
2676  return VisitStaticAssert(node);
2677  default: {
2678  const std::string op_string = op.ToString();
2679  PrintF("\033[31mNo ISEL support for: %s\033[m\n", op_string.c_str());
2680  FATAL("Unexpected operation #%d:%s", node.id(), op_string.c_str());
2681  }
2682  }
2683 
2684  if (trace_turbo_) {
2685  DCHECK(node.valid());
2686  int instruction_start = static_cast<int>(instructions_.size());
2687  instr_origins_[node.id()] = {instruction_start, instruction_end};
2688  }
2689 }

2691 void InstructionSelector::VisitNode(OpIndex node) {
2692  tick_counter_->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
2693  const Operation& op = this->Get(node);
2694  using Opcode = Opcode;
2695  using Rep = RegisterRepresentation;
2696  switch (op.opcode) {
2697  case Opcode::kBranch:
2698  case Opcode::kGoto:
2699  case Opcode::kReturn:
2700  case Opcode::kTailCall:
2701  case Opcode::kUnreachable:
2702  case Opcode::kDeoptimize:
2703  case Opcode::kSwitch:
2704  case Opcode::kCheckException:
2705  // Those are already handled in VisitControl.
2706  DCHECK(op.IsBlockTerminator());
2707  break;
2708  case Opcode::kParameter: {
2709  // Parameters should always be scheduled to the first block.
2710  DCHECK_EQ(this->rpo_number(this->block(schedule(), node)).ToInt(), 0);
2711  MachineType type =
2712  linkage()->GetParameterType(op.Cast<ParameterOp>().parameter_index);
2713  MarkAsRepresentation(type.representation(), node);
2714  return VisitParameter(node);
2715  }
2716  case Opcode::kChange: {
2717  const ChangeOp& change = op.Cast<ChangeOp>();
2718  MarkAsRepresentation(change.to.machine_representation(), node);
2719  switch (change.kind) {
2720  case ChangeOp::Kind::kFloatConversion:
2721  if (change.from == Rep::Float64()) {
2722  DCHECK_EQ(change.to, Rep::Float32());
2723  return VisitTruncateFloat64ToFloat32(node);
2724  } else {
2725  DCHECK_EQ(change.from, Rep::Float32());
2726  DCHECK_EQ(change.to, Rep::Float64());
2727  return VisitChangeFloat32ToFloat64(node);
2728  }
2729  case ChangeOp::Kind::kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin:
2730  case ChangeOp::Kind::kUnsignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin: {
2731  using A = ChangeOp::Assumption;
2732  bool is_signed =
2733  change.kind == ChangeOp::Kind::kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin;
2734  switch (multi(change.from, change.to, is_signed, change.assumption)) {
2735  case multi(Rep::Float32(), Rep::Word32(), true, A::kNoOverflow):
2736  case multi(Rep::Float32(), Rep::Word32(), true, A::kNoAssumption):
2737  return VisitTruncateFloat32ToInt32(node);
2738  case multi(Rep::Float32(), Rep::Word32(), false, A::kNoOverflow):
2739  case multi(Rep::Float32(), Rep::Word32(), false, A::kNoAssumption):
2740  return VisitTruncateFloat32ToUint32(node);
2741  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word32(), true, A::kReversible):
2742  return VisitChangeFloat64ToInt32(node);
2743  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word32(), false, A::kReversible):
2744  return VisitChangeFloat64ToUint32(node);
2745  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word32(), true, A::kNoOverflow):
2746  return VisitRoundFloat64ToInt32(node);
2747  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word32(), false, A::kNoAssumption):
2748  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word32(), false, A::kNoOverflow):
2749  return VisitTruncateFloat64ToUint32(node);
2750  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word64(), true, A::kReversible):
2751  return VisitChangeFloat64ToInt64(node);
2752  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word64(), false, A::kReversible):
2753  return VisitChangeFloat64ToUint64(node);
2754  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word64(), true, A::kNoOverflow):
2755  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word64(), true, A::kNoAssumption):
2756  return VisitTruncateFloat64ToInt64(node);
2757  default:
2758  // Invalid combination.
2759  UNREACHABLE();
2760  }
2761 
2762  UNREACHABLE();
2763  }
2764  case ChangeOp::Kind::kJSFloatTruncate:
2765  DCHECK_EQ(change.from, Rep::Float64());
2766  DCHECK_EQ(change.to, Rep::Word32());
2767  return VisitTruncateFloat64ToWord32(node);
2768  case ChangeOp::Kind::kJSFloat16TruncateWithBitcast:
2769  DCHECK_EQ(Rep::Float64(), change.from);
2770  DCHECK_EQ(Rep::Word32(), change.to);
2771  return VisitTruncateFloat64ToFloat16RawBits(node);
2772  case ChangeOp::Kind::kJSFloat16ChangeWithBitcast:
2773  DCHECK_EQ(Rep::Word32(), change.from);
2774  DCHECK_EQ(Rep::Float64(), change.to);

3330  MarkAsRepresentation(loaded_type.representation(), node);
3331  if (load.kind.maybe_unaligned) {
3332  DCHECK(!load.kind.with_trap_handler);
3333  DCHECK(!load.kind.is_atomic);
3334  if (loaded_type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 ||
3335  InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements()
3336  .IsUnalignedLoadSupported(loaded_type.representation())) {
3337  return VisitLoad(node);
3338  } else {
3339  return VisitUnalignedLoad(node);
3340  }
3341  } else if (load.kind.is_atomic) {
3342  if (load.result_rep == Rep::Word32()) {
3343  return VisitWord32AtomicLoad(node);
3344  } else if (load.result_rep == Rep::Word64()) {
3345  return VisitWord64AtomicLoad(node);
3346  } else if (load.result_rep == Rep::Tagged()) {
3347  return kTaggedSize == 4 ? VisitWord32AtomicLoad(node)
3348  : VisitWord64AtomicLoad(node);
3349  }
3350  } else if (load.kind.with_trap_handler) {
3351  DCHECK(!load.kind.maybe_unaligned);
3352  return VisitProtectedLoad(node);
3353  } else {
3354  return VisitLoad(node);
3355  }
3356  UNREACHABLE();
3357  }

3360  MachineRepresentation rep =
