3363  DCHECK(!store.kind.with_trap_handler);
3364  DCHECK_EQ(store.write_barrier, WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
3365  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 ||
3366  InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements()
3367  .IsUnalignedStoreSupported(rep)) {
3368  return VisitStore(node);
3369  } else {
3370  return VisitUnalignedStore(node);
3371  }
3372  } else if (store.kind.is_atomic) {
3373  if (store.stored_rep.SizeInBytes() == 8) {
3374  return VisitWord64AtomicStore(node);
3375  } else {
3376  DCHECK_LE(store.stored_rep.SizeInBytes(), 4);
3377  return VisitWord32AtomicStore(node);
3378  }
3379  } else if (store.kind.with_trap_handler) {
3380  DCHECK(!store.kind.maybe_unaligned);
3381  return VisitProtectedStore(node);
3382  } else {
3383  return VisitStore(node);

3858 
3859 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT
3860 bool InstructionSelector::ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64(OpIndex node,
3861  int recursion_depth) {
3862  // To compute whether a Node sets its upper 32 bits to zero, there are three
3863  // cases.
3864  // 1. Phi node, with a computed result already available in phi_states_:
3865  // Read the value from phi_states_.
3866  // 2. Phi node, with no result available in phi_states_ yet:
3867  // Recursively check its inputs, and store the result in phi_states_.
3868  // 3. Anything else:
3869  // Call the architecture-specific ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64NoPhis.
3870 
3871  // Limit recursion depth to avoid the possibility of stack overflow on very
3872  // large functions.
3873  const int kMaxRecursionDepth = 100;
3874 
3875  if (const PhiOp* phi = TryCast<PhiOp>(node)) {
3876  if (recursion_depth == 0) {
3877  if (phi_states_.empty()) {
3878  // This vector is lazily allocated because the majority of compilations
3879  // never use it.
3880  phi_states_ = ZoneVector<Upper32BitsState>(
3881  node_count_, Upper32BitsState::kNotYetChecked, zone());
3882  }
3883  }
3884 
3885  Upper32BitsState current = phi_states_[node.id()];
3886  if (current != Upper32BitsState::kNotYetChecked) {
3887  return current == Upper32BitsState::kZero;
3888  }
3889 
3890  // If further recursion is prevented, we can't make any assumptions about
3891  // the output of this phi node.
3892  if (recursion_depth >= kMaxRecursionDepth) {
3893  return false;
3894  }
3895 
3896  // Optimistically mark the current node as zero-extended so that we skip it
3897  // if we recursively visit it again due to a cycle. If this optimistic guess
3898  // is wrong, it will be corrected in MarkNodeAsNotZeroExtended.
3899  phi_states_[node.id()] = Upper32BitsState::kZero;
3900 
3901  for (int i = 0; i < phi->input_count; ++i) {
3902  OpIndex input = phi->input(i);
3903  if (!ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64(input, recursion_depth + 1)) {
3904  MarkNodeAsNotZeroExtended(node);
3905  return false;
3906  }
3907  }
3908 
3909  return true;
3910  }
3911  return ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64NoPhis(node);
3912 }
3913 
3914 void InstructionSelector::MarkNodeAsNotZeroExtended(OpIndex node) {
3915  if (phi_states_[node.id()] == Upper32BitsState::kMayBeNonZero) return;
3916  phi_states_[node.id()] = Upper32BitsState::kMayBeNonZero;
3917  ZoneVector<OpIndex> worklist(zone_);
3918  worklist.push_back(node);
3919  while (!worklist.empty()) {
3920  node = worklist.back();
3921  worklist.pop_back();
3922  // We may have previously marked some uses of this node as zero-extended,
3923  // but that optimistic guess was proven incorrect.
3924  for (OpIndex use : turboshaft_uses(node)) {
3925  if (phi_states_[use.id()] == Upper32BitsState::kZero) {
3926  phi_states_[use.id()] = Upper32BitsState::kMayBeNonZero;
3927  worklist.push_back(use);
3928  }
3929  }
3930  }
3931 }
3932 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT

3936 FrameStateDescriptor* GetFrameStateDescriptorInternal(
3937  Zone* zone, Graph* graph, const FrameStateOp& state) {
3938  const FrameStateInfo& state_info = state.data->frame_state_info;
3939  uint16_t parameters = state_info.parameter_count();
3940  uint16_t max_arguments = state_info.max_arguments();
3941  int locals = state_info.local_count();
3942  int stack = state_info.stack_count();
3943 
3944  FrameStateDescriptor* outer_state = nullptr;
3945  if (state.inlined) {
3946  outer_state = GetFrameStateDescriptorInternal(
3947  zone, graph,
3948  graph->Get(state.parent_frame_state()).template Cast<FrameStateOp>());
3949  }
3950 
3951 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3952  if (state_info.type() == FrameStateType::kJSToWasmBuiltinContinuation) {
3953  auto function_info = static_cast<const JSToWasmFrameStateFunctionInfo*>(
3954  state_info.function_info());
3955  return zone->New<JSToWasmFrameStateDescriptor>(
3956  zone, state_info.type(), state_info.bailout_id(),
3957  state_info.state_combine(), parameters, locals, stack,
3958  state_info.shared_info(), outer_state, function_info->signature());
3959  }
3960 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3961 
3962  return zone->New<FrameStateDescriptor>(
3963  zone, state_info.type(), state_info.bailout_id(),
3964  state_info.state_combine(), parameters, max_arguments, locals, stack,
3965  state_info.shared_info(), state_info.bytecode_array(), outer_state,
3966  state_info.function_info()->wasm_liftoff_frame_size(),
3967  state_info.function_info()->wasm_function_index());
3968 }

3972 FrameStateDescriptor* InstructionSelector::GetFrameStateDescriptor(
3973  OpIndex node) {
3974  const FrameStateOp& state =
3975  this->turboshaft_graph()->Get(node).template Cast<FrameStateOp>();
3976  auto* desc = GetFrameStateDescriptorInternal(instruction_zone(),
3977  this->turboshaft_graph(), state);
3978  *max_unoptimized_frame_height_ =
3979  std::max(*max_unoptimized_frame_height_,
3980  desc->total_conservative_frame_size_in_bytes() +
3981  (desc->max_arguments() * kSystemPointerSize));
3982  return desc;
